The Governor of Anambra State, Professor Chukwuma Charles Soludo has asked those who still hide in the bush to launch attacks on innocent citizens of the state to embrace peace, vowing that no inch of Anambra space will be won by them. In his Easter message to the people made available by his head of media, Joe Anatune, Soludo said, “Let me again reassure you that our dear state will continue to thrive on the trajectory of growth, peace and development despite the current wave of insecurity which is drastically being addressed.” “And in this spirit of Easter, I call on those who are still in the bush to surrender their arms and accept the olive branch which has been offered to them. “Let me reiterate that as a people, we will never cede or yield our homeland to criminals. The irrepressible spirit of the good people of Anambra State shall always triumph” He felicitated with Ndi Anambra on the occasion of the Easter celebrations “the solemn occasion of Easter calls for a self-introspection and deep sober reflection. According to him, the occasion is symbolic because it marks the suffering, crucifixion and resurrection of our Lord Jesus Christ. Soludo that coincidentally Easter Sunday marks exactly a month he assumed office as Governor of Anambra State. He added: “It is, therefore, of utmost importance for us to inculcate and emulate the noble virtues of our Lord Jesus Christ and the symbolism of His Crucifixion in the redemption of mankind. POLL “On this special Easter celebration, I call on everyone of us to imbibe the spirit of this solemn occasion as we rededicate ourselves collectively to the onerous task of building a prosperous, safe and livable homeland for our children, great-grand children and the  generations to come”, Soludo appealed